.TH "query_amp_caps" 9 "query_amp_caps" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
query_amp_caps \- query AMP capabilities
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "u32" query_amp_caps
.BI "(struct hda_codec *codec "  ","
.BI "hda_nid_t nid "  ","
.BI "int direction "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "codec" 12
the HD-auio codec
.IP "nid" 12
the NID to query
.IP "direction" 12
either #HDA_INPUT or #HDA_OUTPUT
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Query AMP capabilities for the given widget and direction.
Returns the obtained capability bits.

When cap bits have been already read, this doesn't read again but
returns the cached value.
